Sign in to the Azure Portal.

Navigate to Virtual Machines → click Create → Azure Virtual Machine.

Basics Tab:

 Subscription: Select your Azure subscription.

 Resource Group: Create or choose an existing one.

 VM Name: Enter a unique name.

 Region: Choose closest to Pune (e.g., Central India).

 Image: Select OS (Windows Server, Ubuntu, etc.).

 Size: Pick based on CPU/RAM needs.

 Authentication: Choose Password or SSH key.

Disks Tab: Select OS disk type (Standard SSD, Premium SSD).

Networking Tab: Configure virtual network, subnet, and public IP.

Management Tab: Enable monitoring, auto-shutdown if needed.

Review + Create: Validate settings → click Create
